                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hicks</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName> (<hi rend="italic">rec’d</hi>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">Feb. 26, 1909</hi>
                        </date>).</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In regard to the matter of the Alsop claim I have received a reply from the
                    Chilean foreign office stating that the antecedents which were called for by the
                    department have been sent to the minister of Chile at Washington, same date.
                    Foreign office adds that principal part of antecedents was stated in
                    communication sent to me by Puga Borne April 9 last, a copy of which I forwarded
                    to the department.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
